cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a new method for automatic detection of standard planes in 3D volumes of fetal brain ultrasound using a convolutional neural network. This involves learning the relationship between a 2D plane image and the transformation parameters required to move that plane towards the location/orientation of the standard plane in the 3D volume. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and fetal development, which suggests that it could also belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a neural network for automatic detection of standard planes in 3D volumes of fetal ultrasound suggests that the paper could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
